data.description: Welcome to this gorgeous 4-bedroom, 2. 5 bath colonial loaded with upgrades nestled in a serene setting backing to woodlands for ultimate privacy. The beauty begins outside as you approach, you'll be greeted by a spacious front porch, perfect for enjoying quiet mornings or evening sunsets. The house offers a sense of privacy as it backs onto lush woods, creating a peaceful retreat for nature enthusiasts. For those with a green thumb, you'll appreciate the beautifully landscaped garden with an in-ground sprinkler system featuring a variety of flowers, planting beds, vegetables, and apple trees in the fenced backyard. A recently replaced deck and a large paver patio is ideal for entertaining and simple relaxation. ****** Inside, an open floor plan, rich hardwood flooring, soaring ceilings, decorative moldings, a gourmet kitchen, gracious owner’s suite, and a fully finished lower level create instant appeal. Fresh neutral paint, new carpet and luxury vinyl plank flooring, and upgrades including a home security system, newer windows, HVAC, roof, tankless hot water heater, an electric car charger, Telsa Solar panels helping to reduce energy costs, and so much more make it move-in ready, all that awaits is you!  ****** As you step inside, the American oak hardwood floors in the open foyer create a warm and inviting atmosphere. To the left, you'll find the formal living room and dining room, ideal for hosting gatherings and special occasions. To the right of the entrance, there's a well-appointed office with built-in shelving, providing a productive workspace, along with a convenient powder room nearby. Moving to the back of the home, you'll discover Danish oak hardwood floors that flow seamlessly the gourmet kitchen that is sure to please the modern chef with gleaming granite countertops, white and beige 42’ cabinets, custom tile backsplashes, cast iron sink, and quality stainless steel appliances, including a 6-burner range and smart refrigerator. The adjoining breakfast area with a striking 2 story ceiling is perfect for casual dining and has a French style door granting access to the deck with descending stairs to the paver patio and fully fenced backyard with wooded acres beyond—truly a private oasis for indoor/outdoor living. Back inside, the family room with a cozy gas fireplace beckons family and friends to gather. ****** Ascend the stairs to the landing overlooking the foyer and family room below and onward to the light filled owner’s suite boasting plush new carpet, a lighted ceiling fan, room for a sitting area, and walk-in closet. The renovated ensuite bath features a furniture style dual sink vanity with matching wall cabinets, a jetted soaking tub, and frameless glass enclosed shower—all coming together to create a private oasis to begin and end the day. Three bright and cheerful bedrooms, each with new carpeting and lighted ceiling fans, share access to the well appointed hall bath, while a laundry room with cabinets on this level adds convenience and eases the daily task. ****** The walkout lower level with gorgeous new luxury vinyl plank flooring and a pool table that conveys features a spacious multipurpose recreation room featuring separate areas for games, media, and exercise, while a storage room with built-in shelving provides loads of storage space completing the comfort and luxury of this beautiful and well maintained home. ****** All this in a peaceful residential community close to an abundance of diverse shopping, dining, and entertainment choices nearby including St. Charles Towne Center, Charles County Plaza, and Waldorf Marketplace, while outdoor enthusiasts will enjoy St. Charles Lake Trail with serene hiking trails. Commuters will appreciate the easy access to major routes including Route 301, Indian Head Highway, Joint Base Andrews, NOVA and Washington, DC. If you’re looking for an exceptional home in a spectacular location, this is it!
